-- Iran's Central Bank to Sell Currencies, Gold to Control Prices, Mehr Says
-- B y   A l i   S h e i k h o l e s l a m i
-- 2010-09-29T12:13:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-29/iran-s-central-bank-to-sell-currencies-gold-to-control-prices-mehr-says.html
Iran’s  central bank  will offer
buyers unlimited amounts of foreign currencies and gold starting
tomorrow, as the prices of the currencies and metal rise, the
state-run  Mehr  news agency reported, citing Vice President
Mohammad Reza Rahimi.  U.S. dollars were sold at 12,200 rials in central Tehran
today, while the bank’s official exchange rate is 10,203, Mehr
said. The lowest dollar-rial rate in the past year was 9,834 on
March 18, while the highest was 10,507 on June 7, according to
the bank’s website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ali Sheikholeslami in London at 
